#eldar.corp.google.comEldar seems to be an internal Googler-only website used for managing internal privacy requests/assessments. While the frontend itself is protected behind ÜberProxy since it&#39;s on *.corp.google.com, the API itself was exposed publicly on eldar-pa.clients6.google.com, allowing non-Googlers to query anything they want.
This was especially interesting due to the nature of information on Eldar. For instance, you could see requests for access to internal Google logs:
