&lt;div class=&quot;separator&quot; style=&quot;clear: both;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEi6uOGCcQghu-ykAadFqAok6chUpuHJkGrN05ql06_o11CWmVsC2tX1X7heph6JNdM410mju8bhT5vxnngCyDGdmbC45nrlbM0KE5xWq1OCEOyydktrsGOXEbM4Q-MxFrxqkTac8fOprj9pKL78ODNdoKBEKy7gVdeUDn_vpWyEzObhJWkRjk36c387JH0/s2048/000007.xwd.png&quot; style=&quot;display: block; padding: 1em 0; text-align: center; &quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; width=&quot;320&quot; data-original-height=&quot;1200&quot; data-original-width=&quot;2048&quot; src=&quot;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEi6uOGCcQghu-ykAadFqAok6chUpuHJkGrN05ql06_o11CWmVsC2tX1X7heph6JNdM410mju8bhT5vxnngCyDGdmbC45nrlbM0KE5xWq1OCEOyydktrsGOXEbM4Q-MxFrxqkTac8fOprj9pKL78ODNdoKBEKy7gVdeUDn_vpWyEzObhJWkRjk36c387JH0/s320/000007.xwd.png&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

The computer will search for itself on the Net.

&lt;div class=&quot;separator&quot; style=&quot;clear: both;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEgvWxJ4q9MZaMwByScYnyJjzZCgBNuURWHUPxjGzbNxH1XWC50yJLczHKKB-i0RoCoBAOt0AQbUvXV_dsOcOdLh1Fm1GvGcRGQXgeGjp-ILAADtO6glTs6Tec9Il1rR-PlxdY-tgF6JwlzEJDguaNHAz1lHj-fd0egMsvvtuLJdrDxHw1JEptpkTZxYFAw/s2048/000008.xwd.png&quot; style=&quot;display: block; padding: 1em 0; text-align: center; &quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; width=&quot;320&quot; data-original-height=&quot;1200&quot; data-original-width=&quot;2048&quot; src=&quot;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEgvWxJ4q9MZaMwByScYnyJjzZCgBNuURWHUPxjGzbNxH1XWC50yJLczHKKB-i0RoCoBAOt0AQbUvXV_dsOcOdLh1Fm1GvGcRGQXgeGjp-ILAADtO6glTs6Tec9Il1rR-PlxdY-tgF6JwlzEJDguaNHAz1lHj-fd0egMsvvtuLJdrDxHw1JEptpkTZxYFAw/s320/000008.xwd.png&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

And Wikipedia does appear, a little misrendered, but legible. It was not quick about it.

&lt;div class=&quot;separator&quot; style=&quot;clear: both;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEjFShJd_wH_ghCuwCAQ5HYL2F11ONzFXo5ZJGUazHw0jqEwaPurxaWtgoXA07_V2gIylmyFWwCDKEM2TtLlXt3AgEeNQAZZdUm-99Y_-JsEbIgSCFc5r6XY-ObTdWbSCXoYQAMwX9wFbuTinIw6t43M6Q-J0wpx1TO_AACTV9D4O9JTGI8t0q2Pg1KmsbY/s2048/000010.xwd.png&quot; style=&quot;display: block; padding: 1em 0; text-align: center; &quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; width=&quot;320&quot; data-original-height=&quot;1200&quot; data-original-width=&quot;2048&quot; src=&quot;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEjFShJd_wH_ghCuwCAQ5HYL2F11ONzFXo5ZJGUazHw0jqEwaPurxaWtgoXA07_V2gIylmyFWwCDKEM2TtLlXt3AgEeNQAZZdUm-99Y_-JsEbIgSCFc5r6XY-ObTdWbSCXoYQAMwX9wFbuTinIw6t43M6Q-J0wpx1TO_AACTV9D4O9JTGI8t0q2Pg1KmsbY/s320/000010.xwd.png&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

It does have JavaScript support through &lt;a href=&quot;https://duktape.org/&quot;&gt;Duktape&lt;/a&gt;, but the DOM and certain other constructs are still works in progress, so it&#39;s not enough for Google either and ended up breaking other things. Although I turned JavaScript off and left it that way, page layout and overall responsiveness were still pretty sluggish &amp;mdash; I&#39;ll gladly exchange poor rendering for faster rendering, but I wasn&#39;t even getting that. Also, NetSurf doesn&#39;t seem to have official support for Gopher, which I personally use quite a bit and would even be appropriate on this hardware.
&lt;p&gt;
So let&#39;s try &lt;a href=&quot;https://dillo.org/&quot;&gt;Dillo&lt;/a&gt;. Fortunately most of its prerequisites were of course already built, including most of them for FLTK (its toolkit). The only component that dragged things out was &lt;tt&gt;wget&lt;/tt&gt;, which invoked a whole bunch of its own GNU-specific prerequisites. It took about a day and change to build everything.

&lt;div class=&quot;separator&quot; style=&quot;clear: both;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEhMtYi8x3qPDs2528oaY_bB3sCVc5QEiZNj4bi-ZOiyam34VNzPZzuqgmviWvNU4nQOxQI2qxJttQpifKo2uM5yyhbwO2NAVv4QwRtQs30u92Z-oxcFmfS_sAm4iKVw87_HdQ2EabZ7MXvYvjsb6RDsm2ASde_Atp9VzIVzTgHhQlSavUU_GyD8ec4ryko/s2048/000015.xwd.png&quot; style=&quot;display: block; padding: 1em 0; text-align: center; &quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; width=&quot;320&quot; data-original-height=&quot;1200&quot; data-original-width=&quot;2048&quot; src=&quot;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEhMtYi8x3qPDs2528oaY_bB3sCVc5QEiZNj4bi-ZOiyam34VNzPZzuqgmviWvNU4nQOxQI2qxJttQpifKo2uM5yyhbwO2NAVv4QwRtQs30u92Z-oxcFmfS_sAm4iKVw87_HdQ2EabZ7MXvYvjsb6RDsm2ASde_Atp9VzIVzTgHhQlSavUU_GyD8ec4ryko/s320/000015.xwd.png&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

Dillo was immediately and noticeably quicker, came up with a sane window size, and helpfully printed logging information to the terminal so I could understand what it was doing. 

&lt;div class=&quot;separator&quot; style=&quot;clear: both;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEigb5ytZo7MmUFNpJck0sYfysw4g52nTic9Ph9iHdyhJkRKtsi4-tlq998r1Afun6ZFKuaMV2NfDEBj8YuWGbSLfq8TYkrJi7LAc_zjqpkCf9U20oeDzJ37xcHlw1EHJHJ4FwQiWcfJYt9_mQZmDMOzJm8qZ9KTp-cNMuOzQrux0GptsrYbQxYiHbN1v74/s2048/000016.xwd.png&quot; style=&quot;display: block; padding: 1em 0; text-align: center; &quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; width=&quot;320&quot; data-original-height=&quot;1200&quot; data-original-width=&quot;2048&quot; src=&quot;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEigb5ytZo7MmUFNpJck0sYfysw4g52nTic9Ph9iHdyhJkRKtsi4-tlq998r1Afun6ZFKuaMV2NfDEBj8YuWGbSLfq8TYkrJi7LAc_zjqpkCf9U20oeDzJ37xcHlw1EHJHJ4FwQiWcfJYt9_mQZmDMOzJm8qZ9KTp-cNMuOzQrux0GptsrYbQxYiHbN1v74/s320/000016.xwd.png&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

Its rendering is not perfect, but it&#39;s good enough for all the sites that matter.

&lt;div class=&quot;separator&quot; style=&quot;clear: both;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEgVi4B1XoyOArVo-4N2pBUGcMTl-cK4oI9epNIXkdvRyQWbSF6NQIOybDz7fuySlrLXc1u8_WhMofbqAXJZWLKWNpjPmngHaiJlabFGaHZgR8wR8CgTgxJQiO4psTfQs8puNWVgZiEbhL86VtSab50f8gG8_nSpSPAPFZbggh4OYhip0LOWlfrKknMO8UU/s2048/000019.xwd.png&quot; style=&quot;display: block; padding: 1em 0; text-align: center; &quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; width=&quot;320&quot; data-original-height=&quot;1200&quot; data-original-width=&quot;2048&quot; src=&quot;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEgVi4B1XoyOArVo-4N2pBUGcMTl-cK4oI9epNIXkdvRyQWbSF6NQIOybDz7fuySlrLXc1u8_WhMofbqAXJZWLKWNpjPmngHaiJlabFGaHZgR8wR8CgTgxJQiO4psTfQs8puNWVgZiEbhL86VtSab50f8gG8_nSpSPAPFZbggh4OYhip0LOWlfrKknMO8UU/s320/000019.xwd.png&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

I did the same &quot;test&quot; in Dillo that I did in NetSurf and got coherent search results ...

&lt;div class=&quot;separator&quot; style=&quot;clear: both;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEjmEWxJIcWuX7dPtpda_qFbB75NqNQuPNaNVhPheelW4DxpMedvlcAlDYQ1NAxolnD1xkKouKrPoxHaIdO1fTWOt0hS07yO3x_kkd_fJdsTZuu2R4BuLbnogpuij5YasRuo4-YKLkVZ4AEb3hBoGCyjVAwtLmLztMdoOAw87_xc6K0VJ_cYrKdUoS7ORlg/s2048/000020.xwd.png&quot; style=&quot;display: block; padding: 1em 0; text-align: center; &quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; width=&quot;320&quot; data-original-height=&quot;1200&quot; data-original-width=&quot;2048&quot; src=&quot;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEjmEWxJIcWuX7dPtpda_qFbB75NqNQuPNaNVhPheelW4DxpMedvlcAlDYQ1NAxolnD1xkKouKrPoxHaIdO1fTWOt0hS07yO3x_kkd_fJdsTZuu2R4BuLbnogpuij5YasRuo4-YKLkVZ4AEb3hBoGCyjVAwtLmLztMdoOAw87_xc6K0VJ_cYrKdUoS7ORlg/s320/000020.xwd.png&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

... and a legible Wikipedia page. NetSurf&#39;s rendering is clearly better, but Dillo does it significantly faster.

&lt;div class=&quot;separator&quot; style=&quot;clear: both;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEiOQ6VUJjIDr2oWWcXGq1-n5tSWCc-PVWsGTx26yB8Trt-hufXnImpD9_B62nwZtA8rLqvC46v2eGdg-nuKvMH8LCc7bchHWRCo_DJ5RpViqj7WfwrjAYYsFFRcPQ2ZDFIVbJWBxnzA0edmAB70Z3ILMQhmiIQ5tgp62qI015HvfP2-p0LWxeDDowlYsT8/s2048/000017.xwd.png&quot; style=&quot;display: block; padding: 1em 0; text-align: center; &quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; width=&quot;320&quot; data-original-height=&quot;1200&quot; data-original-width=&quot;2048&quot; src=&quot;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEiOQ6VUJjIDr2oWWcXGq1-n5tSWCc-PVWsGTx26yB8Trt-hufXnImpD9_B62nwZtA8rLqvC46v2eGdg-nuKvMH8LCc7bchHWRCo_DJ5RpViqj7WfwrjAYYsFFRcPQ2ZDFIVbJWBxnzA0edmAB70Z3ILMQhmiIQ5tgp62qI015HvfP2-p0LWxeDDowlYsT8/s320/000017.xwd.png&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

The other thing that has pushed Dillo into the default slot on this machine is its plugin API, for which &lt;a href=&quot;https://git.dillo-browser.org/plugins/gopher&quot;&gt;Gopher is available&lt;/a&gt;. The plugin support is arguably Dillo&#39;s greatest strength, and I want to play with it some more, but now I can do basic browsing of my own network and services.
&lt;p&gt;
Still, I&#39;ve used NetSurf on other constrained architectures and it shouldn&#39;t be &lt;em&gt;this&lt;/em&gt; bad: that &lt;tt&gt;-O2&lt;/tt&gt; is making what I strongly suspect is a bad compiler for this architecture even worse. Thirty percent faster wouldn&#39;t be a world of difference, but it would be &lt;em&gt;some&lt;/em&gt; difference, getting me almost to the point of building &lt;tt&gt;gcc&lt;/tt&gt; for this and hacking the ports system to use it. Either way you slice it, upgrading the ports tree on this is going to be a pain.

&lt;!--
